reviews.review: It is only fan service. The story is so lame and predictable. It could have been written by some fan-art writer. And, at the same time, is the less bad of the last trilogy. It doesn't speak well of The Rise of Skywalker, instead it does speak poorly of the other two.
By far one of the best movies in the entire saga. Some parts are predictable but great acting and directing brings closure to the Skywalker saga

There're many,many mistakes in this movie (the tendency to exaggerate, differents inconsistencies, the generic plot, the dissociation from the last episode, etc.) One thing that instead is made perfectly is fan service, and also everything who could be emotional is used as plot device.
Yea, Now its time for the next Generation to take up the fight!
This was a solid conclusion to the Skywalker saga filled with action and great fight scenes, especially the Light Saber fights that occurred.
I know a lot of critics are well, critical, however Star Wars TROS really does deliver a great overall end to the story us geeks can get excited over and appreciate.

I liked how much more force powers they used here than in the previous two movies but I did not like the fact that they didn't show Anakin Skywalker's force ghost even though the movie is called "The Rise of Skywalker" and Anakin is one of the most impacting Skywalkers out there next to Luke.

I liked it.  The Skywalker legacy and direction of this film seemed to fit the original narrative started by Lucas more so than the previous narrative with Johnson.  I feel the outrage crowd and critics feel a sense of emptiness that the potential was taken out and momentum faltered.  I see it otherwise, the storyline concludes in a way that feels fitting regardless of small critiques about parts of the movie that I have no experience to critique in the first place.  I liked it, it made me happy, and my childhood was reignited for a couple hours as I watched the legacy of this triple trilogy end with a new purpose.  If you go in wanting that I think you'll get it, if you go in wanting it to be more than the spectacle of a space opera you might be let down.
Loved the final movie! I clapped, cheered, & cried. It was fun, moving, and I'm sad it's over!
